The Congo peafowl (Afropavo congensis), known as the African peafowl or mbulu by the Bak√¥ngo, is a species of peafowl native to the Congo Basin.  It is one of three extant species of peafowl and the only member of the subfamily native to Africa, the other two being the Indian peafowl (originally of India and Sri Lanka) and the green peafowl (native to Myanmar and Indochina).

